diff --git a/docs/oidc_username.md b/docs/oidc_username.md
new file mode 100644
index 0000000..7ab0a19
--- /dev/null
+++ b/docs/oidc_username.md
@@ -0,0 +1,33 @@
+# OIDC Username Support
+
+This feature allows you to configure linkding to use the username field from OIDC claims instead of the email field for user authentication and identification.
+
+## Configuration
+
+To enable this feature, set the following environment variable:
+
+```
+OIDC_USE_USERNAME_FIELD=True
+```
+
+When this option is enabled:
+
+1. User lookup will be performed using the `preferred_username` or `username` field from the OIDC claims instead of the `email` field.
+2. New users will be created with their username set to the value of the `preferred_username` or `username` field.
+3. When sharing bookmarks, the username will be displayed instead of the email address, providing better privacy.
+
+## How it works
+
+The application uses a custom OIDC authentication backend that can use either the email field (default behavior) or the username field based on the configuration.
+
+When `OIDC_USE_USERNAME_FIELD` is set to `True`:
+- The backend will first look for a `preferred_username` claim
+- If not found, it will fall back to the `username` claim
+- User lookup and creation will be based on this username value
+
+When `OIDC_USE_USERNAME_FIELD` is not set or set to `False`:
+- The default behavior is used, which looks up users by email address
+
+## Benefits
+
+The main benefit of this feature is privacy. When users share bookmarks, their username will be displayed instead of their email address, which is more appropriate for sharing with other users or publicly.
